Study & Phone

A snapshot of phone usage during my study sessions

Xin Li

2025-05-11

Studying… or So I Thought?

As a full-time Stage 3 Computer Science student, I feel like I’m always studying - or I shall say, I’m always sitting down with my study ambitions.

Whenever I study at home or on campus, my ritual goes something like this:

  1. Prepare a cup of coffee, hot or iced, with milk, but never sugar.
  2. Pick a random chocolate from the box. Any flavour works, as long as it’s sweet.
  3. Find a sunny spot by the window, preferably with a view of something green.
  4. Review my to-do list and choose a task to kick off.
  5. And finally…. study time (in theory)!

“Today, I shall conquer all the tasks… unless my phone conquers me first.” – Xin Li 😭

Have a coffee and study hard

Yes, I Did Study!

Believe it or not, I have logged 52 study sessions in total! Each session ranged from 50 to 300 minutes (yes, some were longer than I expected - go me!).

As you can see from the graph below, it turns out that I studied the most on Fri, ranking up 13 sessions in that day of the week.

On the flip side, Thu didn’t seem to have much of my study actions… apparently, my brain (unintentionally) took that day off during the week. 😅

My Study Session Counts over the Week

Spoiler: My Phone Is My Best Friend

Now you might be wondering: Did I ever get distracted by my phone during my study sessions? (No doubt here - the answer is obviously yes.)

But how often did it happen? Was I more distracted at certain times of the day? Or am I just… can be easily distracted by my phone whenever?

My logged data is telling me that I generally picked up my phone the most in the Evening(5PM-9PM). Across the 16 sessions during the Evening(5PM-9PM), I reached for my phone a whopping 103 times in total - that’s an average of 6.4 phone pickups per session! 😭

On the brighter side, my most focused time during the day was Morning(6AM-12PM). Across all the 14 study sessions during that period, I picked up my phones 26 times in sum - that’s just 1.9 phone pickups per session. Pretty impressive, right?

Phone Usage Frequency by Study Time of the Day

What Stole My Focus?

Oh well, what was I actually doing on my phone?

Different times of the day, different vibes… and maybe, different distractions, too?

In the morning, I mostly got sidetracked by Chat, taking up 60% of all my phone usage in that time slot.

In the afternnon, my phone time was mostly spent on Chat, which made up 80% of distraction. I guess I might need another coffee to just re-boost my productivity after lunch. 😅

In the evening, I mainly spent my time on phone for Game, stealing away 60% of all focus. Maybe it’s the time for me to unwind…?

And as for the night, when the world goes quiet, it’s my turn to do some Game, which took up 60% of my nighttime phone use.

Hmm… I didn’t realise my distractions had a schedule too!

What is My Main Activity on Phone During the Day

After All…

Here’s a fun fact to wrap things up:

It’s currently 1AM (yes, midnight again) and I’ve been working on this visual story for nearly four hours straight…

And guess what? I’ve only picked up my phone once - just to check the time!

So… what does this tell us?

Maybe… deadlines are stronger than phone distractions? 😭
